arts.ttl: Colchester United claimed 1-0 win at MK Dons in League Two
arts.sum: “It felt like a home game – they were incredible today. "Credit to the subs, because I thought they came on a time when we just looked like we were tiring.

arts.ttl: Colchester United beat Milton Keynes Dons in League Two
arts.sum: Colchester goalkeeper Matt Macey was hardly troubled in the first half but MK Dons came close to scoring just before half-time when former U’s midfielder Alex Gilbey collected Liam Kelly's pass on the edge of the area before curling a shot just wide of the far post. They came agonisingly close to breaking the deadlock in the 56th minute when Gordon collected possession on the edge of the area before curling a delightful shot towards goal that clattered a post, before being cleared.

arts.ttl: Ten-man MK Dons pay the penalty as Colchester’s Jack Payne haunts former club
arts.sum: The midfielder scored a last-gasp penalty to seal all three points for the visitors, while Callum Hendry was dismissed in stoppage time.

arts.ttl: Colchester United travel to play MK Dons in League Two
arts.sum: Colchester United head coach Danny Cowley on MK Dons game: Colchester are hoping Harry Anderson will be available again after he missed the Wimbledon game while the U’s will check on the fitness of midfielder Teddy Bishop who was forced off last weekend due to injury.

arts.ttl: Colchester United defender Ben Goodliffe's full focus is on Southend game time
arts.sum: Goodliffe has so far started four times for the Shrimpers including their 1-1 draw with Tamworth last weekend, as they plot a late play-off push in the National League. Goodliffe told the Southend Echo: "For me it’s about playing games for the time being.

arts.ttl: Former Colchester defender Charlie Daniels linked with vacant League Two role
arts.sum: Daniels, 38, who played 19 times in total for the U’s in the 2021-22 season, is one of a number of names said to be in the running for the role, following Nigel Adkins' departure earlier this week. Tranmere are said to be aware of Daniels' rich potential as a young up and coming English coach, with the former Premier League player impressing in his current role as Watford under-21 boss, in the Professional Development League.

arts.ttl: Danny Cowley outlines key factor behind Colchester's impressive defensive record
arts.sum: “The boys at the front end of the pitch play with such an energy and intensity that even when the ball does come forward, it doesn’t come forward with the same quality. The U’s head to MK Dons on Saturday aiming to extend their unbeaten run in League Two to nine matches and continue the fine form which has seen them establish themselves one of the division’s best defensive teams.
